.RS
.PP
Returns the process identifier (pid) of a new process started by the application of \fIModule:Function\fR to \fIArgs\fR on \fINode\fR. If \fINode\fR does not exist, a useless pid is returned. Otherwise works like \fIspawn_opt/4\fR.

